5000|$|The younger, {{newly arrived}} Americans behave with a {{manifest}} arrogance of power — not only towards The Race, but even towards their own [...] "obsolete" [...] older countrymen {{and women of}} the Admiral Peary. However, representatives of The Race — while embarking on a desperate struggle to catch up and achieve FTL flight for themselves — are able to devise a <b>counter-deterrence</b> even with their existing sub-light ships, coming {{up with the idea of}} launching them to hit Earth at half-light speed, causing horrendous damage dwarfing that of nuclear weapons and possibly destroying Earth altogether or rendering it uninhabitable. The threat of so retaliating for a nuclear strike at Home in effect establishes an interstellar version of mutual assured destruction.|$|E

